The paper deals with task offloading in fog-enabled networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The proposed multi-armed bandit framework involves decision-making under uncertainty, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of a UCB-type algorithm for exploration-exploitation tradeoff is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
